UID:gz-2026-leadership-series-featuring-dr-nathaniel-mike-perry-dean-of-th
 e-college-of-space-intelligence-military-operations-at-columbia-southern-u
 niversity-1663672@southbaldwinchamber.com
DESCRIPTION:Description\nPresented by\nVulcan\, Inc.\n\, the\nLeadership S
 eries\nis one of the South Baldwin Chamber of Commerce’s premier program
 s designed to keep members informed\, engaged\, and connected to the issue
 s shaping our region. Hosted eight times each year\, these luncheons featu
 re respected and influential speakers who bring insight on timely topics i
 mpacting our business community.\nFrom economic development and tourism to
  local governance and state-level initiatives\, each program delivers rele
 vant\, real-world perspective you can take back to your business or organi
 zation. Just as important\, the Leadership Series provides valuable opport
 unities to build relationships with fellow professionals\, civic leaders\,
  and key decision-makers from across South Baldwin County.\nAgenda\n11:00 
 AM: Private Workforce & Top Investors' Meeting\n11:30 AM: Buffet Lunch cat
 ered by\nJim ‘N Nick’s Community BBQ\n12:00 PM: Program Begins\nInvest
 ing in the Future\nWe are proud to recognize our Education Enrichment Spon
 sor\,\nWarren Averett\n\, for helping connect today’s students with tomo
 rrow’s opportunities.\nCommunity Spotlight — Local Nonprofit Partners\
 nWe are honored to highlight two organizations making a meaningful impact 
 across Baldwin County:\nBaldwin County Education Coalition\nJohn McClure S
 nook Family YMCA\n\n---\n🌐 View original event: https://businesshub.sou
 thbaldwinchamber.com/calendar/Details/2026-leadership-series-featuring-dr-
 nathaniel-mike-perry-dean-of-the-college-of-space-intelligence-military-op
 erations-at-columbia-southern-university-1663672
